# Ship lanes (LOCKED — pick by host)

**SSOT doc:** `docs/platform/mac-free-ship-lanes-2026-07.md`  
**D1:** `agentsam_rules_document` id `rule_mac_free_ship_lanes`

## Command matrix

| Where you are | Ship command | Never |
|---------------|--------------|-------|
| **Mac** (desk, plenty of RAM) | `npm run deploy:full` **or** `npm run deploy:fast` | `npm run deploy` alone |
| **GCP iam-tunnel VM** / phone / remote PTY | `npm run ship:remote` (push → CF Builds) | `deploy:full`, `deploy:fast`, Vite, rclone |
| **Cloudflare Workers Builds** | `node scripts/smart-build.mjs` then `npm run deploy:fast:cf` | wrangler-per-file R2 loops |
| **Emergency worker-only** (any host) | `npm run ship:remote -- --worker-only` | Expects SPA/PWA unchanged |

## Hard bans on `iam-tunnel` (GCP)

- **Do not** run `npm run deploy:full`
- **Do not** run `npm run deploy:fast` / Vite / `npm --prefix dashboard run build`
- **Do not** run rclone dashboard sync
- Those OOM/crash the ~1GB VM. Production SPA/PWA ships via **Cloudflare Builds** after `git push`.

## What `ship:remote` does

1. Requires clean tree (commit first).
2. `git push` to `origin/main`.
3. CF Builds: Vite → R2 content-hash delta → wrangler (+ services SW ingest when `PUSH_SERVICE_TOKEN` is set).

## Proof after ship

- `https://inneranimalmedia.com/pwa-build-meta.json` → `git_sha` + `cache_bust`
- Worker post-deploy version key matches pushed SHA when full/fast path ran

MCP server repo is separate: deploy only from `inneranimalmedia-mcp-server` with that repo’s `npm run deploy:full`.
